---

### What happened
- You had TailwindCSS v4 in `client/package.json` with Create React App (`react-scripts`).
- CRA’s PostCSS stack tried to load `tailwindcss` as a PostCSS plugin. In v4 the plugin moved, causing: “It looks like you're trying to use tailwindcss directly as a PostCSS plugin… install @tailwindcss/postcss.”
- Even after adding the v4 plugin, CRA still failed due to broader v4 incompatibilities.
- After switching to Tailwind v3, another error appeared: your CSS used design tokens like `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, and `border-border`, which weren’t defined in v3, so Tailwind couldn’t generate those utilities.

### The error
- Primary: PostCSS plugin mismatch with Tailwind v4 + CRA.
- Secondary: Missing utility classes (`border-border`, `bg-background`, `text-foreground`) because they weren’t defined in the Tailwind theme.

### What I changed to fix it
- Downgraded Tailwind to a CRA-compatible version.
  - `client/package.json`: set `tailwindcss` to `^3.4.17` and removed `@tailwindcss/postcss`.
- Restored PostCSS v3-style config.
  - `client/postcss.config.js`: use `plugins: { tailwindcss: {}, autoprefixer: {} }`.
- Defined your design tokens.
  - `client/tailwind.config.js`: added `background`, `foreground`, `border` under `theme.extend.colors`.
- Verified dev build works; CRA now compiles with only ESLint warnings.

### How to avoid this next time
- Keep framework/bundler and library majors aligned.
  - Tailwind v4 expects the new plugin and works best with modern bundlers (Vite, Next). CRA v5 is better with Tailwind v3.
- Pin or consciously upgrade major versions.
  - Avoid caret bumps to new majors without reviewing release notes; prefer exact versions or use a lockfile and planned upgrades.
- Follow upgrade guides before bumping majors.
  - Tailwind v4 introduced breaking changes to PostCSS integration.
- Define custom tokens explicitly in Tailwind v3.
  - Any class like `bg-background` must exist in `theme.extend.colors`.

If you later want Tailwind v4:
- Migrate off CRA to something like Vite or Next, or confirm CRA supports v4 via community tooling.
- Use `@tailwindcss/postcss` in PostCSS config and follow the v4 docs exactly.

- Dev server is running fine now; only ESLint warnings remain.
